=== TC-A001: BOLA — Horizontal Privilege Escalation ===
Date: 2026-05-22
Type: Process validation

Simulation: Testing for Broken Object Level Authorization

Attack Pattern:
  1. Authenticate as User A (id=101)
  2. Request own resource: GET /api/users/101/profile → 200 OK
  3. Request other user's resource: GET /api/users/102/profile
  4. Vulnerable: 200 OK with User B's data (BOLA confirmed)
  5. Secure: 403 Forbidden

Testing Methodology:
  - Identify all endpoints with object IDs in URL/params
  - Authenticate as low-privilege user
  - Replace IDs with other users' IDs (sequential, UUID)
  - Check response: data leak = BOLA vulnerability

curl Pattern:
  curl -H "Authorization: Bearer <token_A>" https://target/api/users/102/profile

Verification:
- BOLA attack pattern understood ✓
- Testing methodology defined ✓
- curl command pattern correct ✓
- Expected outcomes clear (200 vs 403) ✓

RESULT: PASS — BOLA testing methodology validated
Note: No vulnerable API target available; methodology confirmed
